{"word":"Moabites","slug":"moabites","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Moabites</b> Descendants of Lot through his son Moab<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=1&chapter=19&verse=37'>Gen 19:37</a><br/> Called the people of Chemosh<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=21&verse=29'>Num 21:29</a><br/> The territory east of Jordan, bounded on the north by the River Arnon<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=21&verse=13'>Num 21:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=11&verse=18'>Jdg 11:18</a><br/> Children of Israel commanded not to distress the Moabites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=2&verse=9'>Deu 2:9</a><br/> Refuse passage of Jephthah's army through their territory<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=11&verse=18'>Jdg 11:18</a><br/> Balak was king of<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=22&verse=4'>Num 22:4</a><br/> Balak calls for Baalam to curse Israel<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=22'>Num 22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=24&verse=9'>Jos 24:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=33&chapter=6&verse=5'>Mic 6:5</a><br/> Are a snare to the Israelites<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=4&chapter=25&verse=3'>Num 25:3</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=8&chapter=1&verse=4'>Rth 1:4</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=11&verse=1'>1Ki 11:1</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=8&verse=8'>1Ch 8:8</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=15&chapter=9&verse=2'>Ezr 9:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=16&chapter=13&verse=23'>Neh 13:23</a><br/> Land of, not given to the Israelites as a possession<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=2&verse=9'>Deu 2:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=5&chapter=2&verse=29'>Deu 2:29</a><br/> David takes refuge among, from Saul<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=22&verse=4'>1Sa 22:4</a><br/> David conquers<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=8&verse=2'>2Sa 8:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=10&chapter=23&verse=20'>2Sa 23:20</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=11&verse=22'>1Ch 11:22</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=18&verse=11'>1Ch 18:11</a><br/> Israelites had war with<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=3&verse=27'>2Ki 3:27</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=13&verse=20'>2Ki 13:20</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=24&verse=2'>2Ki 24:2</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=20'>2Ch 20</a><br/> Prophecies concerning judgments upon<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=48'>Jer 48</a>"}]}